        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2009-01-30T06:36:19.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>The Editor dijit will not work without Javascript. Internally, it is represented by two elements,a textarea and a hidden element. Client-side, Dojo changes the textarea into a custom JS widget, removing the textarea entirely, and an onSubmit event writes the content of the dijit to the hidden element -- which Zend_Dojo_Form_Element_Editor then uses as the value.</p>

<p>This is one area where we cannot gracefully degrade, unfortunately.</p>

